---

## 7. Functional Requirements (FR)

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| FR-001 | Display all revenue KPIs (Labor/Parts/Oil/Tires) |
| FR-002 | Provide Actual vs Target comparison |
| FR-003 | Allow filtering by: Brand, Branch, Month, Year, Model |
| FR-004 | Show full workshop profit |
| FR-005 | Highlight underperformance with color coding |
| FR-006 | Display model ranking based on Parts net sales |
| FR-007 | Auto-exclude Warranty & Internal job cards |
| FR-008 | Auto-clean negative or invalid entries |
| FR-009 | Show daily/monthly summary cards |
| FR-010 | Drill through to Job Cards |

---

## 8. Non-Functional Requirements (NFR)

- **Performance:** Load time < 6 seconds  
- **Accuracy:** Must match Finance numbers within 0.1%  
- **Security:** Access limited to After Sales & Finance  
- **Scalability:** Should support additional branches  
- **Reliability:** Daily refresh must run automatically  

---

## 9. Constraints

- Different ERP databases per brand  
- Missing model codes in some entries  
- Monthly target dependent on Finance updates  
- Variances may occur if job cards closed late  
- Inconsistent naming conventions in raw data  

---

## 10. Risks

- Incorrect Brand/Model mapping  
- Duplicate job cards  
- Late posting from Finance  
- Direct Sales mistakenly merged into Parts revenue  

---

## 11. Deliverables

- Power BI Dashboard (After Sales Performance)  
- Unified Fact & Dimension tables  
- SQL transformations  
- Data dictionary  
- Business rules documentation  
- End-user guide  

---

## 12. Future Enhancements

- Add cost-based profitability  
- Add technician productivity KPIs  
- Add hourly labor rate KPI  
- Add warranty performance dashboard  
- Enable year-over-year comparison  

